  "source_notes": "Sy Scholfield cites mother's record quoted in \"The Collected Works of Samuel Taylor Coleridge: Abbt to Byfield, Volume 1\" (Routledge, 1980), p. 413: \"p ~2, in SC's hand October 11th (1830). Herbert Coleridge, son of Henry Nelson & Sara Coleridge, was born at Hampstead, at a little past 11 in the forenoon.\" However, apparently October \"11th\" is a typo because Sarah Coleridge (Sara's mother), who was in attendance at the birth, wrote of the birth on the 8th of October: \"On October 8, she described the event to Poole: \"Yesterday forenoon, about 11 o'clock Sara was safely brought to bed of a boy...\" (\"Sara Coleridge, a Victorian Daughter: Her Life and Essays\" by Bradford Keyes Mudge, Yale University Press, 1989, p. 54).\\n",
